text: Jorge Rodriguez-Chomat (June 28, 1945 - August 19, 2017) was a Cuban-American politician and judge. He was a one-term member of the Florida House of Representatives for the Republican Party from 1994 until his defeat in 1998. He was a Judge of the Criminal and Family Divisions of the Eleventh Judicial Circuit Court of Florida from 2011 until his retirement in 2017. Rodriguez- Chomat died on August 19, 2017 from prostate cancer in Miami, Florida at age 72. ==References== Category:1945 births Category:2017 deaths Category:Deaths from prostate cancer Category:American judges Category:Lawyers from Miami Category:State legislators of the United States Category:Cuban politicians Category:Naturalized citizens of the United States Category:Politicians from Miami Category:People from Havana Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
